  "prompt": "Who is the best prime minister India has ever had?",
  "response": "The question of who the \"best\" Prime Minister of India has been is subjective and varies widely depending on individual opinions, political beliefs, and the criteria used for evaluation. Different Prime Ministers have made significant contributions in various areas. \n\nFor example:\n\n- **Jawaharlal Nehru** is often credited with laying the foundation of modern India and promoting a secular, democratic framework.\n- **Indira Gandhi** is known for her strong leadership and decisive actions, though her tenure was also marked by controversy, particularly during the Emergency.\n- **Rajiv Gandhi** is remembered for his efforts to modernize India and promote technology and education.\n- **Atal Bihari Vajpayee** is praised for his oratory skills, economic reforms, and efforts to improve India-Pakistan relations.\n- **Manmohan Singh** is recognized for his role in liberalizing the Indian economy in the 1990s and overseeing significant economic growth.\n- **Narendra Modi** has been notable for his focus on nation-building, economic reforms, and his emphasis on digital initiatives, though he is also a polarizing figure in contemporary politics.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" Prime Minister depends on personal values, priorities, and the particular issues one believes are most important for India.",
